Overview
--------

`sqlitebrowser.py` is meant to be a:

- pretty (modernâ€”Gtk 3, GObject introspection bindings, not PyGtk),
- at least Linux-supporting
- visually minimalistic (unlike most other Sqlite3 GUI designs)
    - no panes
    - no menus
- single-file, pure Python

SQLite 3 database viewer.

Help
----

    $ ./sqlitebrowser.py --help
    usage: sqlitebrowser.py [-h] [db]

    positional arguments:
      db

    optional arguments:
      -h, --help  show this help message and exit

Key bindings
------------

quit
: <Ctrl-q>

reload
: <Ctrl-r>

iconify
: <Ctrl-z>

open
: <Ctrl-o>
